Yemen: Millions of children could be pushed to the brink of starvation due to huge funding shortfalls for humanitarian aid amid the #COVID19 pandemic.

@UNICEF appeals for urgent support to provide lifesaving assistance to children in desperate need.

https://t.co/DCgGdpBNRm

43 tonnes of essential supplies to fight #COVID19 have arrived in Yemen, which is in the midst of an unprecedented humanitarian crisis.

@WFP &amp; partners are distributing the supplies to hospitals &amp; laboratories across the country. https://t.co/B0EUkoHk63

https://t.co/PgTtlBitGK

What is the future YOU want? 

@UNYouthEnvoy is calling on young people from 15 to 29 to share ideas about the future in short essay competition. 📝 

Deadline is 29 June. Details: https://t.co/arSeDDeywJ https://t.co/4FN3SJ8WnM

1 billion children are affected by violence every year - and #COVID19 is only making it worse - by limiting access to services &amp; support systems.

@UNICEF &amp; partners are calling on countries to put in place new strategies to keep children safe. 

https://t.co/0yeJTsmTh9

Older people have the highest rates of serious illness &amp; death from the #coronavirus.

@UNOCHA shows how organizations are adapting measures to ensure older people have access to services &amp; support during the #COVID19 pandemic.
https://t.co/cNLMUBid9o

Mozambique: After two devastating cyclones &amp; large-scale flooding, #COVID19 is exacerbating food insecurity in the country.

@WFP is providing lifesaving assistance, including access to nutritious food for the sustainable recovery of family livelihoods. 
https://t.co/1GBxDrLElF
